ructor, even though that would not verify \\\"any visibility.\\\" I'm thinking it might be best to avoid direct reflection, relying instead on the public API methods `setService` and `getServices` for robustness.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_a97MSTp1orGhPTcJKuK1YwGq|fc_02a217922f96b34d0169f6b64aeda881969d49f96743046be0", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src -path '*/src/test/java/*.java' | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 878, "output": 751, "cacheRead": 11776, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 13405, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777776189905, "responseId": "resp_02a217922f96b34d0169f6b63e40848196937252238e4890a7"}}
